In February 2006 a team of forensic scientists announced the beginning of a six-month study to assess bone and skin remains from a museum at Chinon and reputed to be those of Joan of Arc. The study cannot provide a positive identification but could rule out some types of hoax through carbon dating and gender determination.17 (Accessed 1 March 2006)↩
