According to medieval clothing expert Adrien Harmand, she wore two layers of pants (trousers in British-English) attached to the doublet with twenty fastenings. The outer pants were made of a boot-like leather. &quot;Jeanne d'Arc, son costume, son armure.&quot; 21 (Accessed 23 March 2006)↩
